my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Use of goggles, face shield and/or mask throughout operation; 
b) Use of other PPE including protecting long sleeve clothing to prevent skin injuries, safety shoes and gloves; 
c) Persons not engaged in a job should stay clear; 
d) Caution should be paid to other people working in the vicinity, adjust the working angle/position of the tool to prevent debris flying towards them; 
e) Dust mask should be used if dust is generated during the activity.

a) Crew must be instructed how to use a tool in safe manner, consult manufacturer’s operation manual accordingly; 
b) All tool safety guards must be in place; 
c) The working tool must be switched off when not being used; 
d) Worn or damaged tools must not be used; 
e) Ensure the most appropriate tool for the job is being used and accessories / pieces are of adequate type (drill bits, grinding & cutting disks, etc.) and in good condition / properly connected; 
f) Cutting edges should be kept sharp and clean; 
g) Adequate illumination must always be provided.

a) Hands should be kept dry, particularly when connecting cables and switching on/off a tool; 
b) Tool cables should not come in contact with water; 
c) When working in open spaces and precipitation occurs a job should be stopped and tools collected into a safe dry place; 
d) Damaged equipment should never be used; 
e) Extension cables should be placed in such a position that it cannot get damaged by other equipment, when passed through a door or hatch.

a) All tool safety guards must be in place; 
b) Use of PPE (face shield, long sleeve boiler suit, etc.);
c) All flammable materials should be removed from working area, if not possible then protective screens should be installed.
d) If in an enclosed space the appropriate risk assessment must be consulted as well as a valid work permit in place with full compliance of the enclosed space entry procedures. Oxygen content must never fall below the minimum.

a) Tools should be used for jobs they have been designed for; 
b) Operators must be capable of using the required tool; 
c) The tools used must be off appropriate size to that of the job.

a) Ear defenders and / or plugs must be worn at all times; 
b) More frequent breaks and job rotation must be considered to reduce the duration and effects associated with exposure; 
c) Ensure there is no wear & tear or misalignment of components that could increase exposure levels. 
d) Consider other available work methods with less or no exposure effects that can be used to complete the task.

a) Good house keeping must always be a priority to the working area. 
b) Tools should be stowed in a tidy 'ship shape' manner when not in use; 
c) After the job is completed all tools should be collected and put back in their designated storing places; ensure tools are not left lying around the deck.
